        <updateDate>2020-08-10T17:32:13Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Main Street Revival Act</strong> <b>of 2020</b></p> <p> This bill allows a specified small business to elect to pay its first-year employment taxes in four equal installments. The bill defines <i>specified small business</i> as any HUBZone business (a business operating in a historically underutilized business zone as defined by the Small Business Act) that is not reasonably expected to employ more than 25 full-time employees in its first year of operation.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
